oraListenerTable.name: oraListenerTable
oraListenerTable.description: The table of information about the generic network listeners installed on a system.

oraListenerEntry.name: oraListenerEntry
oraListenerEntry.description: An entry for a single generic network listener on the host.

oraListenerIndex.name: oraListenerIndex
oraListenerIndex.description: A numeric index, unique among all the generic listeners on this host.

oraListenerName.name: oraListenerName
oraListenerName.description: The name of this generic listener.

oraListenerVersion.name: oraListenerVersion
oraListenerVersion.description: The version number of this generic listener, in vendor specific format.

oraListenerStartDate.name: oraListenerStartDate
oraListenerStartDate.description: The date and time at which ths generic listener was started.

oraListenerUptime.name: oraListenerUptime
oraListenerUptime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the generic listener was last started.

oraListenerTraceLevel.name: oraListenerTraceLevel
oraListenerTraceLevel.description: indicates the level of detail the trace facility the generic listener records for events. The greater the level is, the more detailed the level of tracing is.

oraListenerSecurityLevel.name: oraListenerSecurityLevel
oraListenerSecurityLevel.description: indicates whether the generic listener is password-protected or not. If security is 'on', password is required to perform certain DBA tasks asgainst the listener using the listener control utility. If security is 'off', password is not required.

oraListenerParameterFile.name: oraListenerParameterFile
oraListenerParameterFile.description: indicates the name of the file to which configuration information is stored. Default is $ORACLE_HOME/network/admin/ <listener_name>.ora.

oraListenerLogFile.name: oraListenerLogFile
oraListenerLogFile.description: indicates the directory in which to find the log file that is automatically generated for listener events. Default is operating system specific; on UNIX, for example, it is $ORACLE_HOME/network/log.

oraListenerTraceFile.name: oraListenerTraceFile
oraListenerTraceFile.description: indicates the name of the file to which trace information is written. Default is $ORACLE_HOME/network/trace/<listener_name>.trc.

oraListenerState.name: oraListenerState
oraListenerState.description: indicates the current state of the generic listener. 'down' indicates that the generic listener is not available for any use, but is know to the agent. 'up' indicates that the generic listener is running and available for generic use. This would be inspected by an agent on receipt of an oraListenerState trap.

oraListenerNumberOfServices.name: oraListenerNumberOfServices
oraListenerNumberOfServices.description: indicates the number of different types services: dedicated sever, dispatcher, or prespawned shadow, configured with the generic listener.

oraListenerContact.name: oraListenerContact
oraListenerContact.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed listener, together with information on how to contact this person.

oraSIDTable.name: oraSIDTable
oraSIDTable.description: The table of information about the SIDs of the databases for whom the listener listens on. The system identifier (SID) specifies the ORACLE System ID of the database server.

oraSIDEntry.name: oraSIDEntry
oraSIDEntry.description: An entry relating a SID to a generic listener.

oraSIDListenerIndex.name: oraSIDListenerIndex
oraSIDListenerIndex.description: A numeric index, unique among all the generic listeners.

oraSIDName.name: oraSIDName
oraSIDName.description: The name of the SID. There is a one-to-one correspondence between database and SID.

oraSIDCurrentConnectedClients.name: oraSIDCurrentConnectedClients
oraSIDCurrentConnectedClients.description: indicates the total number of currently connected clients thru this SID.

oraSIDReservedConnections.name: oraSIDReservedConnections
oraSIDReservedConnections.description: indicates the total number of reserved connections for clients on this SID.

oraDedicatedSrvTable.name: oraDedicatedSrvTable
oraDedicatedSrvTable.description: The table of the dedicated servers associated with an system identifier (SID) of the database.

oraDedicatedSrvEntry.name: oraDedicatedSrvEntry
oraDedicatedSrvEntry.description: An entry relating a dedicated server to a SID. The table is indexed first by oraSIDName, and then oraDedicatedSrvIndex so that all dedicated servers associated with a given SID can be found by SNMP traversal operations (get-next and get-bulk).

oraDedicatedSrvIndex.name: oraDedicatedSrvIndex
oraDedicatedSrvIndex.description: A numeric index, unique among all the dedicated servers.

oraDedicatedSrvEstablishedConnections.name: oraDedicatedSrvEstablishedConnections
oraDedicatedSrvEstablishedConnections.description: indicates how many incoming connection requests have been accepted by the dedicated server.

oraDedicatedSrvRejectedConnections.name: oraDedicatedSrvRejectedConnections
oraDedicatedSrvRejectedConnections.description: indicates how many incoming connection requests have been rejected by the dedicated server.

oraDispatcherTable.name: oraDispatcherTable
oraDispatcherTable.description: The table of the dispatchers associated with an system identifier (SID) of the database.

oraDispatcherEntry.name: oraDispatcherEntry
oraDispatcherEntry.description: An entry relating a dispatcher to a SID. The table is indexed first by oraSIDName, and then oraDispatcherIndex so that all dispatchers associated with a given SID can be found by SNMP traversal operations (get-next and get-bulk).

oraDispatcherIndex.name: oraDispatcherIndex
oraDispatcherIndex.description: A numeric index, unique among all the dispatchers.

oraDispatcherEstablishedConnections.name: oraDispatcherEstablishedConnections
oraDispatcherEstablishedConnections.description: indicates how many incoming connection requests have been accepted by the dispatcher.

oraDispatcherRejectedConnections.name: oraDispatcherRejectedConnections
oraDispatcherRejectedConnections.description: indicates how many incoming connection requests have been rejected by the dispatcher.

oraDispatcherCurrentConnections.name: oraDispatcherCurrentConnections
oraDispatcherCurrentConnections.description: indicates the number of connection requests currently being redirected to the dispatcher.

oraDispatcherMaximumConnections.name: oraDispatcherMaximumConnections
oraDispatcherMaximumConnections.description: indicates the greatest number of connection requests that will ever be accepted by the dispatcher.

oraDispatcherState.name: oraDispatcherState
oraDispatcherState.description: indicates the current state of the dispatcher. 'blocked' indicates that the dispatcher is temporarily not accepting redirected connectioin requests. 'ready' indicates that the dispacher is ready to accept any redirected conenction requests.

oraDispatcherProtocolInfo.name: oraDispatcherProtocolInfo
oraDispatcherProtocolInfo.description: indicates the protocol of the dispatcher listens on as well as protocol specific information. The exact format will be vendor and host specific.

oraPrespawnedSrvTable.name: oraPrespawnedSrvTable
oraPrespawnedSrvTable.description: The table of the prespawned servers associated with a SID.

oraPrespawnedSrvEntry.name: oraPrespawnedSrvEntry
oraPrespawnedSrvEntry.description: An entry relating a prespawned server to a SID. The table is indexed first by oraSIDName, and then oraPrespawnedSrvIndex so that all prespawned servers associated with a given SID can be found by SNMP traversal operations (get-next and get-bulk).

oraPrespawnedSrvIndex.name: oraPrespawnedSrvIndex
oraPrespawnedSrvIndex.description: A numeric index, unique among all the prespawned servers.

oraPrespawnedSrvEstablishedConnections.name: oraPrespawnedSrvEstablishedConnections
oraPrespawnedSrvEstablishedConnections.description: indicates how many incoming connection requests have been accepted by the prespawned server.

oraPrespawnedSrvRejectedConnections.name: oraPrespawnedSrvRejectedConnections
oraPrespawnedSrvRejectedConnections.description: indicates how many incoming connection requests have been rejected by the prespawned server.

oraPrespawnedSrvCurrentConnections.name: oraPrespawnedSrvCurrentConnections
oraPrespawnedSrvCurrentConnections.description: indicates the number of connection requests currently being redirected to the prespawned server.

oraPrespawnedSrvMaximumConnections.name: oraPrespawnedSrvMaximumConnections
oraPrespawnedSrvMaximumConnections.description: indicates the greatest number of connection requests that will ever be accepted by the prespawned server.

oraPrespawnedSrvState.name: oraPrespawnedSrvState
oraPrespawnedSrvState.description: indicates the current state of the prespawned server. 'blocked' indicates that the prespawned server is temporarily not accepting redirected connection requests. 'ready' indicates the prespawned server is ready to accept any redirected conenction requests.

oraPrespawnedSrvProtocolInfo.name: oraPrespawnedSrvProtocolInfo
oraPrespawnedSrvProtocolInfo.description: indicates the protocol of the prespawned server listens on as well as protocol specific information. The exact format will be vendor and host specific.

oraPrespawnedSrvProcessorID.name: oraPrespawnedSrvProcessorID
oraPrespawnedSrvProcessorID.description: indicates the process ID of the prespawned server.

oraListenAddressTable.name: oraListenAddressTable
oraListenAddressTable.description: The table of information about the addresses that the listener is listening at.

oraListenAddressEntry.name: oraListenAddressEntry
oraListenAddressEntry.description: An entry relating the listen addresses to a generic listener.

oraListenAddressIndex.name: oraListenAddressIndex
oraListenAddressIndex.description: A numeric index, unique among all the listen addresses.

oraListenAddress.name: oraListenAddress
oraListenAddress.description: The addresses to whom the listener is listening at.

oraListenerStateChange.name: oraListenerStateChange
oraListenerStateChange.description: An rdbmsStateChange trap signifies that one of the generic listeners managed by this agent has changed its oraListenerState in a way that makes it less accessible for use.
